# Tauri dev watcher ignore rules.
#
# The dev watcher (tauri dev) recursively watches this whole `src-tauri`
# directory and, at the file-event level, only honors `.taurignore` rules — the
# CLI's builtin ignore list (target/, gen/, node_modules/) is applied only while
# enumerating the top-level folders, NOT to change events. Without the rules
# below, churn-prone metadata inside the vendored forks triggers an endless
# kill+relaunch ("reloading and reloading") loop.
#
# Root cause this file fixes: the vendored `tauri-fork` is its own git repo with
# Git's fsmonitor daemon active, which constantly rewrites
# `tauri-fork/.git/fsmonitor--daemon/cookies`. Every write was being seen as a
# source change and rebuilt the app forever.

# Git metadata for the repo and any vendored/nested repos (fsmonitor daemon
# cookies, index, refs, logs, etc.) — never a reason to rebuild the app.
.git/
**/.git/

# Build outputs and generated schemas (already excluded from the initial walk,
# repeated here so they are also ignored as change events).
target/
target-test/
gen/
node_modules/

# OS noise.
.DS_Store
